i><li><span class="action-link" data-social-service="print" data-social-trigger="actionBar"><svg class="icon print-icon"><use xlink:href="#mono-icon-print"></use></svg><span>Print</span></span></li></ul></div></ps-actionbar> </div>    <div data-element="story-body"> <div class="story-stack-item" id="1" data-target ><div class="story-stack-item-number"  data-hide-number ><span>1</span></div>  <div  class="story-stack-story">     <div data-element="story-stack-story-body" class="ct-rich-text-children font-body font-normal text-lg leading-7.75 text-primary-text-color clearfix"> <p>Every wonderful thing deserves a similarly wonderful follow-up. Dinner? Dessert. Hot sauna? Ice bath. “Paddington”? “Paddington 2.” Movie sequels aside, under Southern California’s sunshine, there may be nothing better than a hard-earned libation after a trek. What’s a workout without a reward?</p> <p>Here’s my 30-pack of hikes and local breweries, from easy urban jaunts to challenging summits, paired with craft beverages near each trailhead. Consider this a list of nature strolls and watering holes — or trails and ales — and add some of your own. Beers change regularly (so don’t panic if they’re out of my recommended brew) as do hours.</p> <p>In the meantime, go with the grain, and hop from west to (y)east (or the reverse) on these 30 thirst-quenching L.A. crawls. Cheers!</p><div class="enhancement" data-click="enhancement"
    
