-social">  <div class="phone poi-module-phone"><span class="icon phone-icon-087da1" aria-label="phone"></span> <a class="link phone" href="tel:6617239463" data-social-service="phone" >(661) 723-9463 </a> </div>   <div class="website poi-module-website"><span class="icon globe-icon-087da1"></span> <a class="link" href="https://thiefandbarrel.wine/" target="_blank" >website</a> </div>   <div class="instagram poi-module-instagram"><span class="icon instagram-icon-087da1"></span> <a class="link" href="https://instagram.com/thiefandbarrel" target="_blank" >instagram</a> </div>  </div>  <div class="postal-address"><svg class="icon postal-address-icon map-marker"><use xlink:href="#icon-map-marker"></use></svg><div><a href="https://maps.apple.com/?q=34.65173%2C-118.141182" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span class="street postal-address-street"> 42257 6th St. W No. 302, </span><span class="city postal-address-city"> Lancaster, </span><span class="state postal-address-state"> California </span><span class="zipcode postal-address-zipcode"> 93534 </span></a></div></div> <div class="poi-module-more-info"> More Info </div></div></div></div> </div>  </div></div>   </div><p> </p><p>Where can you find California’s most iconic desert species, most photographed spring flowers and most important aquatic engineering system?</p><div class="enhancement" data-click="enhancement"
    
        data-align-center
    
><div class="google-dfp-ad-wrapper" style="min-height: 270px" data-min-height="270" ><div class="google-dfp-ad-caption">Advertisement</div><div id="google-adcda7be46-7889-4044-85c2-0e6f2cc6af57" class="google-dfp-ad injected" data-slot-name="/21787098806/web.latimes/travel/storystack_inline"  data-slot-sizes="[[300, 250], [728, 90], [970, 250], [970, 90]]"  data-ad-type="injected"  data-slot-ad-size-maps="[[[1024, 0], [728, 90], [970, 250], [970, 90]], [[0, 0], [300, 250]]]"  data-module-targeting="{&quot;position&quot;:&quot;2&quot;}" ><span class="google-dfp-ad-placeholder"></span></div></div></div><p> </p> <p>Lancaster, L.A.’s high desert home base, best known for its astonishing orange bloom blanket (in good years) at the Antelope Valley California Poppy Reserve, is the place. The area also is worthy of a visit during less-visited months when temperatures are cool. Check out a three-mile stroll through <a class="link" href="https://www.cityoflancasterca.org/our-city/departments-services/parks-recreation-arts/parks-and-facilities/prime-desert-woodland-preserve" target="_blank" >Prime Desert Woodland Preserve</a> that captures the local essence of the high desert. You’ll find signs to inform you about the landscape at the 120-acre preserve, maneuver through the densest grove of Joshua trees around (they aren’t actually trees but yucca) and various local flora, such as an 800-year old creosote bush. Check out the interpretive center to learn more about the history and find art exhibits. </p> <p>Next stop: Lancaster libations. For beer, hit up <a class="link" href="https://braverybrewing.com/" target="_blank" >Brävery Brewing</a>, known for its comprehensive house tap list. One highlight is the variety of barrel-aged iterations of its flagship stout (from bourbon to brandy to Islay scotch to tequila). For wine, <a class="link" href="https://thiefandbarrel.wine/" target="_blank" >Thief &amp; Barrel</a> serves sweet and dry whites, reds, and specialty offerings.</p> <p></p> </div>   </div>  </div><div class="story-stack-item" id="4" data-target ><div class="story-stack-item-number"  data-hide-number ><span>4</span></div>  <div  class="story-stack-story">  <h3 class="story-stack-story-title">Downtown L.A. and Arts District breweries</h3>     <div data-element="story-stack-story-body" class="ct-rich-text-children font-body font-normal text-lg leading-7.75 text-primary-text-color clearfix"> <div class="enhancement" data-click="enhancement"
    
        data-align-center
    
>   <div class="column-container two-column-container-5050" >  <div class="column-container-row two-column-container-5050-row">  <div class="column-container-column two-column-container-5050-column" data-click="5050col1"> <div class="module poi-module" data-click="poi"  data-map-marker-id="0000017d-160a-d6ef-a9fd-df6feac50001"   data-map-marker-longitude="-118.23318"   data-map-marker-latitude="34.05095"   data-map-marker-title="Downtown Ale Trail"   data-module-neighborhood="Arts District"     data-module-hike-difficulty="Easy"     data-module-hike-length="3.75"   data-module-category="parks-trails" data-module-subcategory="Urban Trail" data-module-subcategory-filter-id="parks-trails_00000178-1e5a-dff5-abff-de5a13ce0000" data-module-id="0000017d-160a-d502-a1ff-bf4fd2bb0000"><div class="poi-module-flex container-media">  <div class="media poi-module-media">   <div class="image poi-module-image"> <figure class="figure"> <picture >    <source  type="image/webp"  srcset="https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/c7555f5/2147483647/strip/true/crop/3264x2176+0+136/resize/320x213!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F15%2F7c%2F61c21fc2437b8aace0e41267d8ce%2Fpp-tr-ales-and-trails-downtown-urban-walk-62.jpg 320w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/3906348/2147483647/strip/true/crop/3264x2176+0+136/resize/568x379!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F15%2F7c%2F61c21fc2437b8aace0e41267d8ce%2Fpp-tr-ales-and-trails-downtown-urban-walk-62.jpg 568w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/b26ff09/2147483647/strip/true/crop/3264x2176+0+136/resize/768x512!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F15%2F7c%2F61c21fc2437b8aace0e41267d8ce%2Fpp-tr-ales-and-trails-downtown-urban-walk-62.jpg 768w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/14990bc/2147483647/strip/true/crop/3264x2176+0+136/resize/1024x683!/