l=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F08%2Ff7%2F6f429bbd49dd85a2c28a5061048f%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-paperback.jpg 1200w"  sizes="85vw"    width="1200"   height="800"  src="https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/81f9b2f/2147483647/strip/true/crop/3024x2016+0+1008/resize/1200x800!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F08%2Ff7%2F6f429bbd49dd85a2c28a5061048f%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-paperback.jpg" decoding="async"  loading="lazy"  >  </picture>   <div class="figure-content"> <div class="figure-credit">(Matt Pawlik)</div> </div>  </figure> </div>   </div>  </div><div class="poi-module-flex container-content"><div class="poi-module-flex container-content-block">  <h2 class="title poi-module-title"> Paperback Brewing Co. </h2>  <div class="poi-module-categories"><span class="poi-module-categories-icon"><span class="icon category restaurants-icon-fff"></span> </span><span class="neighborhood poi-module-categories-neighborhood"> Glendale </span>   <span class="cuisine poi-module-categories-cuisine"> Brewery </span>    </div>        <div data-element="description" class="ct-body-1 ct-rich-text-children font-service font-light text-base mt-3"><b>Our favorite 🍺: </b>Bunny With a Chainsaw (Hazy Double IPA) and A Milkshake Orange (Milkshake IPA)<br><br><b>Hours:</b> 4 to 10 p.m. Tuesdays to Thursdays; 4 to 11 p.m. Fridays; noon to 11 p.m. Saturdays; noon to 10 p.m. Sundays</div>    <div class="social poi-module-social">   <div class="website poi-module-website"><span class="icon globe-icon-087da1"></span> <a class="link" href="https://www.paperback.la/" target="_blank" >website</a> </div>   <div class="instagram poi-module-instagram"><span class="icon instagram-icon-087da1"></span> <a class="link" href="https://instagram.com/paperbackbrewing" target="_blank" >instagram</a> </div>  </div>  <div class="postal-address"><svg class="icon postal-address-icon map-marker"><use xlink:href="#icon-map-marker"></use></svg><div><a href="https://maps.apple.com/?q=34.130089%2C-118.261888" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span class="street postal-address-street"> 422 Magnolia Ave., </span><span class="city postal-address-city"> Glendale, </span><span class="state postal-address-state"> California </span><span class="zipcode postal-address-zipcode"> 91204 </span></a></div></div> <div class="poi-module-more-info"> More Info </div></div></div></div> </div>  </div></div>   </div><p> </p><p>We love L.A., from the South Bay to the Valley, from the Westside to the Eastside. While Randy Newman covers a lot of iconic Angeleno stomping grounds in his ode to the city, he forgets to mention <a class="link" href="https://www.laparks.org/griffithpark/" target="_blank" >Griffith Park</a> (in his defense, it’s a hard rhyme; we forgive you, Randy). </p><div class="enhancement" data-click="enhancement"
    
        data-align-center
    
><div class="google-dfp-ad-wrapper" style="min-height: 270px" data-min-height="270" ><div class="google-dfp-ad-caption">Advertisement</div><div id="google-ada1459643-46ec-4902-ab20-ad897ac4dad0" class="google-dfp-ad injected" data-slot-name="/21787098806/web.latimes/travel/storystack_inline"  data-slot-sizes="[[300, 250], [728, 90], [970, 250], [970, 90]]"  data-ad-type="injected"  data-slot-ad-size-maps="[[[1024, 0], [728, 90], [970, 250], [970, 90]], [[0, 0], [300, 250]]]"  data-module-targeting="{&quot;position&quot;:&quot;4&quot;}" ><span class="google-dfp-ad-placeholder"></span></div></div></div><p> </p> <p>Explore the county’s largest and most famous park on a 5.25-mile lollipop loop that balances landmark locales and hidden havens. Start at the Fern Dell Nature Museum trailhead, near a stream surrounded by sycamores, coastal redwoods and exotic ferns. Take the East Observatory trail on the ascent (save the West for descent). Find the Charlie Turner trailhead and Berlin Forest before heading right at a junction to go to Dante’s View, a vista-heavy garden planted by volunteers in the 1960s. Continue to Mt. Hollywood (1,625 feet). On the descent, loop down the alternate path to Captain’s Roost (another garden spot) and the best views of the Hollywood sign to the west. </p> <p>For a beer, head to nearby craft giant <a class="link" href="https://www.goldenroad.la/" target="_blank" >Golden Road Brewing</a> for some grub and brews at their massive space. For a lesser-known option, head to <a class="link" href="https://www.paperback.la/" target="_blank" >Paperback Brewing Co.</a>, a new joint located in a World War II-era aircraft hangar, for a tasting flight. Better yet, go to both.</p> <p></p> </div>   </div>  </div><div class="story-stack-item" id="7" data-target ><div class="story-stack-item-number"  data-hide-number ><span>7</span></div>  <div  class="story-stack-story">  <h3 class="story-stack-story-title">North Etiwanda Preserve and Joseph Filippi Winery &amp; Vineyards</h3>     <div data-element="story-stack-story-body" class="ct-rich-text-children font-body font-normal text-lg leading-7.75 text-primary-text-color clearfix"> <div class="enhancement" data-click="enhancement"
    
        data-align-center
    
>   <div class="column-container two-column-container-5050" >  <div class="column-container-row two-column-container-5050-row">  <div class="column-container-column two-column-container-5050-column" data-click="5050col1"> <div class="module poi-module" data-click="poi"  data-map-marker-id="0000017d-0b5c-d3be-a57d-2ffdb2100000"   data-map-marker-longitude="-117.523385"   data-map-marker-latitude="34.161997"   data-map-marker-title="North Etiwanda Preserve"   data-module-neighborhood="Rancho Cucamonga"     data-module-hike-difficulty="Easy"     data-module-hike-length="3.25"   data-module-category="parks-trails" data-module-subcategory="Urban Trail" data-module-subcategory-filter-id="parks-trails_00000178-1e5a-dff5-abff-de5a13ce0000" data-module-id="0000017d-0b5c-d502-a1ff-af5fa16b0000"><div class="poi-module-flex container-media">  <div class="media poi-module-media">   <div class="image poi-module-image"> <figure class="figure"> <picture >    <source  type="image/webp"  srcset="https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/724e227/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/320x213!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe8%2F2c%2Fc8ca17b344fda861c6386df259c2%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-north-etiwanda-preserve-26.JPG 320w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/c0859a0/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/568x379!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe8%2F2c%2Fc8ca17b344fda861c6386df259c2%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-north-etiwanda-preserve-26.JPG 568w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/99fd0c0/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/768x512!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe8%2F2c%2Fc8ca17b344fda861c6386df259c2%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-north-etiwanda-preserve-26.JPG 768w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dim