83f1479d8968a2a0bac5f9c5%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-frogtown-brewery.jpg 1024w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/580efa9/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/1200x800!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Feb%2Fb7%2F93d583f1479d8968a2a0bac5f9c5%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-frogtown-brewery.jpg 1200w"  sizes="85vw"    width="1200"   height="800"  src="https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/580efa9/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/1200x800!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Feb%2Fb7%2F93d583f1479d8968a2a0bac5f9c5%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-frogtown-brewery.jpg" decoding="async"  loading="lazy"  >  </picture>   <div class="figure-content"> <div class="figure-credit">(Matt Pawlik)</div> </div>  </figure> </div>   </div>  </div><div class="poi-module-flex container-content"><div class="poi-module-flex container-content-block">  <h2 class="title poi-module-title"> Frogtown Brewery </h2>  <div class="poi-module-categories"><span class="poi-module-categories-icon"><span class="icon category restaurants-icon-fff"></span> </span><span class="neighborhood poi-module-categories-neighborhood"> Elysian Valley </span>   <span class="cuisine poi-module-categories-cuisine"> Brewery </span>    </div>        <div data-element="description" class="ct-body-1 ct-rich-text-children font-service font-light text-base mt-3"><b>Our favorite 🍺:</b> Hazy River (Hazy IPA), Kinky (Blonde Ale), Coconaut (Toasted Coconut Porter)<br><br><b>Hours:</b> 4 to 10 p.m. Mondays to Thursdays; noon to 11 p.m. Fridays and Saturdays; noon to 10 p.m. Sundays</div>    <div class="social poi-module-social">  <div class="phone poi-module-phone"><span class="icon phone-icon-087da1" aria-label="phone"></span> <a class="link phone" href="tel:3234522739" data-social-service="phone" >(323) 452-2739 </a> </div>   <div class="website poi-module-website"><span class="icon globe-icon-087da1"></span> <a class="link" href="https://www.frogtownbrewery.com/" target="_blank" >website</a> </div>   <div class="instagram poi-module-instagram"><span class="icon instagram-icon-087da1"></span> <a class="link" href="https://instagram.com/frogtownbrewery" target="_blank" >instagram</a> </div>  </div>  <div class="postal-address"><svg class="icon postal-address-icon map-marker"><use xlink:href="#icon-map-marker"></use></svg><div><a href="https://maps.apple.com/?q=34.106976%2C-118.251264" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span class="street postal-address-street"> 2931 Gilroy St., </span><span class="city postal-address-city"> Los Angeles, </span><span class="state postal-address-state"> California </span><span class="zipcode postal-address-zipcode"> 90039 </span></a></div></div> <div class="poi-module-more-info"> More Info </div></div></div></div> </div>  </div></div>   </div><p> </p><div class="enhancement" data-click="enhancement"
    
        data-align-center
    
><div class="google-dfp-ad-wrapper" style="min-height: 270px" data-min-height="270" ><div class="google-dfp-ad-caption">Advertisement</div><div id="google-adeb61fbf8-1d93-4e95-acf5-05963ea13585" class="google-dfp-ad injected" data-slot-name="/21787098806/web.latimes/travel/storystack_inline"  data-slot-sizes="[[300, 250], [728, 90], [970, 250], [970, 90]]"  data-ad-type="injected"  data-slot-ad-size-maps="[[[1024, 0], [728, 90], [970, 250], [970, 90]], [[0, 0], [300, 250]]]"  data-module-targeting="{&quot;position&quot;:&quot;6&quot;}" ><span class="google-dfp-ad-placeholder"></span></div></div></div><p> </p><p>There are many starting and ending points along the 51-mile L.A. River. This hike in the centerpoint in the Elysian Valley offers an easy 2-mile journey through an area (and namesake brewery) called Frogtown. </p> <p>Park and walk through the Great Heron Gates to Rattlesnake Park, heading east along the riverbank. First signs of Frogtown graffiti are on your left, inspired no doubt by the once-common resident amphibians (that might have actually been toads). As you hike (or bike) along the paved path that follows the shallow waters of the riparian environment, look for cormorants, stilts and local mascot great blue herons among the willows. You’ll pass Frogtown Brewery after just 0.3 miles, but save it for the return trip. Instead, head under State Route 2 and take a detour at Marsh Park, a grassy recreation area with workout machines and frog statues. Continue along the L.A. River Greenway Trail past Spoke Bicycle Cafe and turn around at Elysian Valley Gateway Park next to local coffee roastery La Colombe. </p> <p>Back at <a class="link" href="https://www.frogtownbrewery.com/" target="_blank" >Frogtown Brewery</a>, enjoy the riverside space that showcases local artwork and features interesting (Pain Killer, a tiki-inspired IPA) and classic ales.</p><div class="enhancement" data-click="enhancement"
    
        data-align-center
    
>  <div class="html-module" data-click="htmlModule"  data-module-id="0000017d-3574-db9b-a37f-b7fd017e0009"><center><button id="myBtn"><a href="#top" style="color: black">Back to the top</a></button>
</div>  </div><p> </p> <p></p> </div>   </div>  </div><div class="story-stack-item" id="10" data-target ><div class="story-stack-item-number"  data-hide-number ><span>10</span></div>  <div  class="story-stack-story">  <h3 class="story-stack-story-title">Los Angeles State Historic Park and Highland Park Brewery</h3>     <div data-element="story-stack-story-body" class="ct-rich-text-children font-body font-normal text-lg leading-7.75 text-primary-text-color clearfix"> <div class="enhancement" data-click="enhancement"
    
        data-align-center
    
