icon map-marker"><use xlink:href="#icon-map-marker"></use></svg><div><a href="https://maps.apple.com/?q=33.8804933%2C-117.8135744" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span class="street postal-address-street"> Buena Vista Ave. and Vista Del Lago, </span><span class="city postal-address-city"> Yorba Linda, </span><span class="state postal-address-state"> California </span><span class="zipcode postal-address-zipcode"> 92886 </span></a></div></div> <div class="poi-module-more-info"> More Info </div></div></div></div> </div>   <div class="column-container-column two-column-container-5050-column" data-click="5050col2"> <div class="module poi-module" data-click="poi"  data-map-marker-id="0000017d-14de-d3be-a57d-3eff6d2e0001"   data-map-marker-longitude="-117.79671"   data-map-marker-latitude="33.85972"   data-map-marker-title="Honey Pot Meadery"   data-module-neighborhood="Anaheim"      data-module-cuisines="Meadery"    data-module-category="restaurants" data-module-id="0000017d-14de-d502-a1ff-bddf60d90000"><div class="poi-module-flex container-media">  <div class="media poi-module-media">   <div class="image poi-module-image"> <figure class="figure"> <picture >    <source  type="image/webp"  srcset="https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/ed751dc/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/320x213!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F1f%2F3ad9051b4614babbc337d69847a1%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-honeypot-meadery.JPG 320w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/29ca52d/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/568x379!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F1f%2F3ad9051b4614babbc337d69847a1%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-honeypot-meadery.JPG 568w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/4c8ec34/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/768x512!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F1f%2F3ad9051b4614babbc337d69847a1%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-honeypot-meadery.JPG 768w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/315ca06/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/1024x683!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F1f%2F3ad9051b4614babbc337d69847a1%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-honeypot-meadery.JPG 1024w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/d8ff2eb/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/1200x800!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F1f%2F3ad9051b4614babbc337d69847a1%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-honeypot-meadery.JPG 1200w"  sizes="85vw"  >     <img class="image" alt="A person next to a Honeypot Meadery sign"  srcset="https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/f879307/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/320x213!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F1f%2F3ad9051b4614babbc337d69847a1%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-honeypot-meadery.JPG 320w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/4d9c409/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/568x379!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F1f%2F3ad9051b4614babbc337d69847a1%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-honeypot-meadery.JPG 568w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/b314526/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/768x512!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F1f%2F3ad9051b4614babbc337d69847a1%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-honeypot-meadery.JPG 768w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/c05d1f0/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/1024x683!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F1f%2F3ad9051b4614babbc337d69847a1%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-honeypot-meadery.JPG 1024w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/964e009/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/1200x800!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F1f%2F3ad9051b4614babbc337d69847a1%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-honeypot-meadery.JPG 1200w"  sizes="85vw"    width="1200"   height="800"  src="https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/964e009/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/1200x800!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F1f%2F3ad9051b4614babbc337d69847a1%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-honeypot-meadery.JPG" decoding="async"  loading="lazy"  >  </picture>   <div class="figure-content"> <div class="figure-credit">(Matt Pawlik)</div> </div>  </figure> </div>   </div>  </div><div class="poi-module-flex container-content"><div class="poi-module-flex container-content-block">  <h2 class="title poi-module-title"> Honey Pot Meadery </h2>  <div class="poi-module-categories"><span class="poi-module-categories-icon"><span class="icon category restaurants-icon-fff"></span> </span><span class="neighborhood poi-module-categories-neighborhood"> Anaheim </span>   <span class="cuisine poi-module-categories-cuisine"> Meadery </span>    </div>        <div data-element="description" class="ct-body-1 ct-rich-text-children font-service font-light text-base mt-3"><b>Our favorite </b>🍷<b>: </b>Shuriken (Meadowfoam Mead), Mead-a-rita (Orange Blossom Mead)<br><br><b>Hours:</b> to 10 p.m. Fridays; noon to 10 p.m. Saturdays; noon to 6 p.m. Sundays</div>    <div class="social poi-module-social">  <div class="phone poi-module-phone"><span class="icon phone-icon-087da1" aria-label="phone"></span> <a class="link phone" href="tel:7143120911" data-social-service="phone" >(714) 312-0911 </a> </div>   <div class="website poi-module-website"><span class="icon globe-icon-087da1"></span> <a class="link" href="https://honeypotmeadery.com/" target="_blank" >website</a> </div>   <div class="instagram poi-module-instagram"><span class="icon instagram-icon-087da1"></span> <a class="link" href="https://instagram.com/honeypotmeadery" target="_blank" >instagram</a> </div>  </div>  <div class="postal-address"><svg class="icon postal-address-icon map-marker"><use xlink:href="#icon-map-marker"></use></svg><div><a href="https://maps.apple.com/?q=33.85972%2C-117.79671" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span class="street postal-address-street"> 5120 E. La Palma Ave., Suite 104, </span><span class="city postal-address-city"> Anaheim, </span><span class="state postal-address-state"> California </span><span class="zipcode postal-address-zipcode"> 92807 </span></a></div></div> <div class="poi-module-more-info"> More Info </div></div></div></div> </div>  </div></div>   </div><p> </p><p>Head to Yorba Linda in northern Orange County for this 2.75-mile loop around the secret Yorba Linda Lakebed Park. Few people know about this park with an inconspicuous trailhead off Buena Vista Avenue. </p> <p>You’ll see many resident art projects scattered throughout the trail, such as the painted rocks with positive messages. This adds to the charm of the hike, which meanders under willows and oaks along a now dry lakebed. There are also multiple spur trails to explore the riparian environment at will. At the southern end of the park, the trail follows a ridge and ascends to the high point of the 90-acre park that once hosted a reservoir. Check out wide-angle views of suburbia and a surprising sample of oil derrick pumps, and search the skies for red-tailed hawks. </p> <p>After the hidden hike, make a beeline for <a class="link" href="https://honeypotmeadery.com/" target="_blank" >Honey Pot Meadery</a>, which serves mead (dry, sweet, fruited, spiced and so on) as well as house-made fruit wines, seltzers and ciders. We liked Shuriken, aged in bourbon barrels, or the Mead-a-rita, an orange blossom mead featuring agave and lime. Prefer a beer? Go next door to veteran-owned <a class="link" href="https://www.allamericanbrewworks.com/" target="_blank" >All-American Brew Works</a>, where we recommend Storm the Beach (Red Ale with Coconut) and Liberty or Death (Peanut Butter Porter).</p><div class="enhancement" data-click="enhancement"
    
        data-align-center
    
