ims4/default/7dc5ccb/2147483647/strip/true/crop/3024x2016+0+477/resize/1024x683!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8d%2F54%2F531aac1c41199ca55c3b30f8106e%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-claremont-breweries-63.JPG 1024w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/330c8ab/2147483647/strip/true/crop/3024x2016+0+477/resize/1200x800!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8d%2F54%2F531aac1c41199ca55c3b30f8106e%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-claremont-breweries-63.JPG 1200w"  sizes="85vw"    width="1200"   height="800"  src="https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/330c8ab/2147483647/strip/true/crop/3024x2016+0+477/resize/1200x800!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8d%2F54%2F531aac1c41199ca55c3b30f8106e%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-claremont-breweries-63.JPG" decoding="async"  loading="lazy"  >  </picture>   <div class="figure-content"> <div class="figure-credit">(Natalie Seffer)</div> </div>  </figure> </div>   </div>  </div><div class="poi-module-flex container-content"><div class="poi-module-flex container-content-block">  <h2 class="title poi-module-title"> Claremont Craft Ales </h2>  <div class="poi-module-categories"><span class="poi-module-categories-icon"><span class="icon category restaurants-icon-fff"></span> </span><span class="neighborhood poi-module-categories-neighborhood"> Claremont </span>   <span class="cuisine poi-module-categories-cuisine"> Brewery </span>    </div>        <div data-element="description" class="ct-body-1 ct-rich-text-children font-service font-light text-base mt-3"><b>Our favorite 🍺:</b> Jacaranda (Rye IPA), Peppers and Peaches (West Coast IPA), Raspberry Gose (Sour)<br><br><b>Hours:</b> 3 to 9 p.m. Tuesdays through Thursdays; 3 to 10 p.m. Fridays; 1 to 10 p.m. Saturdays; 1 to 8 p.m. Sundays.</div>    <div class="social poi-module-social">  <div class="phone poi-module-phone"><span class="icon phone-icon-087da1" aria-label="phone"></span> <a class="link phone" href="tel:9096255350" data-social-service="phone" >(909) 625-5350 </a> </div>   <div class="website poi-module-website"><span class="icon globe-icon-087da1"></span> <a class="link" href="http://www.claremontcraftales.com/" target="_blank" >website</a> </div>   <div class="instagram poi-module-instagram"><span class="icon instagram-icon-087da1"></span> <a class="link" href="https://instagram.com/claremontcraftales" target="_blank" >instagram</a> </div>  </div>  <div class="postal-address"><svg class="icon postal-address-icon map-marker"><use xlink:href="#icon-map-marker"></use></svg><div><a href="https://maps.apple.com/?q=34.108969%2C-117.701847" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span class="street postal-address-street"> 1420 N. Claremont Blvd. No 204C, </span><span class="city postal-address-city"> Claremont, </span><span class="state postal-address-state"> California </span><span class="zipcode postal-address-zipcode"> 91711 </span></a></div></div> <div class="poi-module-more-info"> More Info </div></div></div></div> </div>  </div></div>   </div><p> </p><p>“There is science, logic, reason; there is thought verified by experience. And then there is California.” Whether positive or negative, author and environmental activist Edward Abbey knew California was special. And so do we. </p> <p>Enter a golden state of mind at the <a class="link" href="https://www.calbg.org/" target="_blank" >California Botanic Garden</a> (formerly known as the Rancho Santa Ana Botanic Garden) in Claremont to take a two-mile loop to explore the 86-acre garden filled with California originals just north of the Claremont Colleges. Grab a map at the entrance to find your way among 22,000 specimens (and more than 2,000 species) in meadows as well as Tongva huts and a palm oasis. All of the state’s major ecosystems are represented here: chaparral, desert, pine forests, to name a few), making for a truly satisfying experience we think Abbey would’ve enjoyed too. Iconic Joshua trees and legendary Torrey pines in one hike? California, here we come. If you yearn for more, add on a hike in Claremont Hills Wilderness Park at the base of the San Gabriels, which offers a good workout and phenomenal views. </p> <p>For a local beer garden, head to nearby <a class="link" href="http://www.claremontcraftales.com/" target="_blank" >Claremont Craft Ales</a>, an award-winning cozy spot that has brews with flowery names, such as their flagship Jacaranda. Another option: Head a mile east to neighboring Upland to try a flight from Last Name Brewing; don’t miss its amber lager, Pomona Queen.</p> </div>   </div>  </div><div class="story-stack-item" id="17" data-target ><div class="story-stack-item-number"  data-hide-number ><span>17</span></div>  <div  class="story-stack-story">  <h3 class="story-stack-story-title">Monrovia Canyon and Pacific Plate Brewing Co.</h3>     <div data-element="story-stack-story-body" class="ct-rich-text-children font-body font-normal text-lg leading-7.75 text-primary-text-color clearfix"> <div class="enhancement" data-click="enhancement"
    
        data-align-center
    
>   <div class="column-container two-column-container-5050" >  <div class="column-container-row two-column-container-5050-row">  <div class="column-container-column two-column-container-5050-column" data-click="5050col1"> <div class="module poi-module" data-click="poi"  data-map-marker-id="0000017c-f1e6-d385-abfc-f7eebb3d0000"   data-map-marker-longitude="-118.00114"   data-map-marker-latitude="34.1486"   data-map-marker-title="Monrovia Canyon"   data-module-neighborhood="Monrovia"     data-module-hike-difficulty="Moderate"     data-module-hike-length="6.5"   data-module-category="parks-trails" data-module-subcategory="Urban Trail" data-module-subcategory-filter-id="parks-trails_00000178-1e5a-dff5-abff-de5a13ce0000" data-module-id="0000017c-f1e6-d385-abfc-f7ee96420000"><div class="poi-module-flex container-media">  <div class="media poi-module-media">   <div class="image poi-module-image"> <figure class="figure"> <picture >    <source  type="image/webp"  srcset="https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/7c65a45/2147483647/strip/true/crop/3400x2267+0+1417/resize/320x213!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fdc%2F04%2F425c9eaa4d188568a7f51538292b%2Fpp-tr-ales-and-trails-monrovia-canyon-hike-74.jpg 320w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/4d32065/2147483647/strip/true/crop/3400x2267+0+1417/resize/568x379!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fdc%2F04%2F425c9eaa4d188568a7f51538292b%2Fpp-tr-ales-and-trails-monrovia-canyon-hike-74.jpg 568w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/4e8cc85/2147483647/strip/true/crop/3400x2267+0+1417/resize/768x512!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fdc%2F04%2F425c9eaa4d188568a7f51538292b%2Fpp-tr-ales-and-trails-monrovia-canyon-hike-74.jpg 768w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/4807346/2147483647/strip/true/crop/3400x2267+0+1417/resize/1024x683!