-trails-monrovia-breweries.JPG 1024w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/4f8ba86/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/1200x800!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7b%2Ffa%2F099cfeaa47bc853b104fdf448f25%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-monrovia-breweries.JPG 1200w"  sizes="85vw"    width="1200"   height="800"  src="https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/4f8ba86/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/1200x800!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7b%2Ffa%2F099cfeaa47bc853b104fdf448f25%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-monrovia-breweries.JPG" decoding="async"  loading="lazy"  >  </picture>   <div class="figure-content"> <div class="figure-credit">(Matt Pawlik)</div> </div>  </figure> </div>   </div>  </div><div class="poi-module-flex container-content"><div class="poi-module-flex container-content-block">  <h2 class="title poi-module-title"> Pacific Plate Brewing Co. </h2>  <div class="poi-module-categories"><span class="poi-module-categories-icon"><span class="icon category restaurants-icon-fff"></span> </span><span class="neighborhood poi-module-categories-neighborhood"> Monrovia </span>   <span class="cuisine poi-module-categories-cuisine"> Brewery </span>    </div>        <div data-element="description" class="ct-body-1 ct-rich-text-children font-service font-light text-base mt-3"><b>Our favorite 🍺:</b> Horchata Stout<br><br><b>Hours: </b>4 to 11 p.m. Mondays to Fridays; noon to 11 p.m. Saturdays and Sundays</div>    <div class="social poi-module-social">  <div class="phone poi-module-phone"><span class="icon phone-icon-087da1" aria-label="phone"></span> <a class="link phone" href="tel:6262398456" data-social-service="phone" >(626) 239-8456 </a> </div>   <div class="website poi-module-website"><span class="icon globe-icon-087da1"></span> <a class="link" href="https://www.pacificplatebrewing.com/" target="_blank" >website</a> </div>   <div class="instagram poi-module-instagram"><span class="icon instagram-icon-087da1"></span> <a class="link" href="https://instagram.com/pacificplatebrewery" target="_blank" >instagram</a> </div>  </div>  <div class="postal-address"><svg class="icon postal-address-icon map-marker"><use xlink:href="#icon-map-marker"></use></svg><div><a href="https://maps.apple.com/?q=34.128141%2C-118.002157" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span class="street postal-address-street"> 2015 S. Myrtle Ave., </span><span class="city postal-address-city"> Monrovia, </span><span class="state postal-address-state"> California </span><span class="zipcode postal-address-zipcode"> 91016 </span></a></div></div> <div class="poi-module-more-info"> More Info </div></div></div></div> </div>  </div></div>   </div><p> </p><div class="enhancement" data-click="enhancement"
    
        data-align-center
    
><div class="google-dfp-ad-wrapper" style="min-height: 270px" data-min-height="270" ><div class="google-dfp-ad-caption">Advertisement</div><div id="google-ad04f2b5c8-2ec5-4f49-9f6b-2a3befc92a0c" class="google-dfp-ad injected" data-slot-name="/21787098806/web.latimes/travel/storystack_inline"  data-slot-sizes="[[300, 250], [728, 90], [970, 250], [970, 90]]"  data-ad-type="injected"  data-slot-ad-size-maps="[[[1024, 0], [728, 90], [970, 250], [970, 90]], [[0, 0], [300, 250]]]"  data-module-targeting="{&quot;position&quot;:&quot;10&quot;}" ><span class="google-dfp-ad-placeholder"></span></div></div></div><p> </p><p>Monrovia is known for its idyllic charm, for its extensive experience as a Hollywood backdrop and as home to the headquarters of Trader Joe’s. The perfect small-town escape from the big city is best experienced on a 6.5-mile Fountain to Falls trail that explores the picturesque streets of Old Town and the beautiful forest above. </p> <p>Start at the library park (look for a massive Moreton Bay fig tree and a Mark Twain statue) and follow the signs for the part-urban, part-nature trail. The path begins on suburban roads past Victorian and Arts and Crafts homes (and maybe the occasional curious mule deer) before reaching the Monrovia Canyon Park entrance and nature center. Enjoy an interpretive display, a statue of the town’s unofficial black bear mascot (Samson, who once roamed the streets), and awe-inspiring vistas of Monrovia and the valley beyond. Find the trail behind the nature center under glorious Jeffrey pines and coast live oaks to continue 1.5 miles to the tranquil waterfalls. </p> <p>After backtracking to Old Town, visit one of four breweries, all within walking distance. We love the hop-forward creativity and library-adjacent tap room of <a class="link" href="https://www.hopsecretbrewing.com/" target="_blank" >Hop Secret</a>, the funky art and dark beers at <a class="link" href="https://www.wingwalkerbrewing.com/" target="_blank" >Wingwalker</a>, the friendly atmosphere and refreshing ales at <a class="link" href="https://www.overtownbrew.com/" target="_blank" >Over Town Brewing Co.</a>, and the delicious offerings at <a class="link" href="https://www.pacificplatebrewing.com/" target="_blank" >Pacific Plate</a> (Tom Yum beer, anyone?). Try all to get a truly comprehensive taste of Monrovia.</p><div class="enhancement" data-click="enhancement"
    
        data-align-center
    
>  <div class="html-module" data-click="htmlModule"  data-module-id="0000017d-357c-de0e-ab7f-7f7c5cbe0001"><center><button id="myBtn"><a href="#top" style="color: black">Back to the top</a></button></div>  </div><p> </p> <p></p> </div>   </div>  </div><div class="story-stack-item" id="18" data-target ><div class="story-stack-item-number"  data-hide-number ><span>18</span></div>  <div  class="story-stack-story">  <h3 class="story-stack-story-title">Mt. Lowe and Mt. Lowe Brewing Co.</h3>     <div data-element="story-stack-story-body" class="ct-rich-text-children font-body font-normal text-lg leading-7.75 text-primary-text-color clearfix"> <div class="enhancement" data-click="enhancement"
    
        data-align-center
    
>   <div class="column-container two-column-container-5050" >  <div class="column-container-row two-column-container-5050-row">  <div class="column-container-column two-column-container-5050-column" data-click="5050col1"> <div class="module poi-module" data-click="poi"  data-map-marker-id="0000017d-0aab-d3be-a57d-2eeb57510000"   data-map-marker-longitude="-118.16"   data-map-marker-latitude="34.19"   data-map-marker-title="Mt. Lowe"   data-module-neighborhood="Altadena"     data-module-hike-difficulty="Strenuous"     data-module-hike-length="5.5"   data-module-category="parks-trails" data-module-subcategory="Mountain Trail" data-module-subcategory-filter-id="parks-trails_00000178-1e40-d754-a57a-fe664bbd0002" data-module-id="0000017d-0aab-d502-a1ff-afef45c30000"><div class="poi-module-flex container-media">  <div class="media poi-module-media">   <div class="image poi-module-image"> <figure class="figure"> <picture >    <source  type="image/webp"  srcset="https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/9922d5e/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/320x213!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff0%2F3a%2F705954924fa4bde6aa575246e7e9%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-mt-lowe-hike-12.JPG 320w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/e0cec4c/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/568x379!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff0%2F3a%2F705954924fa4bde6aa575246e7e9%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-mt-lowe-hike-12.JPG 568w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/501e4e5/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/768x512!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff0%2F3a%2F705954924fa4bde6aa575246e7e9%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-mt-lowe-hike-12.JPG 768w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/fd4960f/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0