om%2Ff0%2F3a%2F705954924fa4bde6aa575246e7e9%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-mt-lowe-hike-12.JPG 1200w"  sizes="85vw"    width="1200"   height="800"  src="https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/e9f9a9b/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/1200x800!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff0%2F3a%2F705954924fa4bde6aa575246e7e9%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-mt-lowe-hike-12.JPG" decoding="async"  loading="lazy"  >  </picture>   <div class="figure-content"> <div class="figure-credit">(Matt Pawlik)</div> </div>  </figure> </div>   </div>  </div><div class="poi-module-flex container-content"><div class="poi-module-flex container-content-block">  <h2 class="title poi-module-title"> Mt. Lowe </h2>  <div class="poi-module-categories"><span class="poi-module-categories-icon"><span class="icon category parks-trails-icon-fff"></span> </span><span class="neighborhood poi-module-categories-neighborhood"> Altadena </span>  <span class="poi-module-categories-hike-type"> Mountain Trail </span>   </div>  <div class="poi-module-hike poi-module-social">  <div class="poi-module-hike-distance"><span class="icon poi-module-hike-icon-ruler-000" aria-label="distance"></span> <span>5.5-mile loop</span></div>   <div class="poi-module-hike-difficulty"><span class="icon poi-module-hike-icon-gauge-000" aria-label="difficulty"></span> <span>Strenuous</span></div>   <div class="poi-module-hike-elevation"><span class="icon poi-module-hike-icon-mountain-000" aria-label="elevation"></span> <span>1,300 feet</span></div>  </div>     <div data-element="description" class="ct-body-1 ct-rich-text-children font-service font-light text-base mt-3">Start on Eaton Saddle Trailhead on Mt. Wilson/Red Box Road. Free parking. Dog-friendly.<br><br><b>Distance from brewery:</b> 29 miles</div>    <div class="postal-address"><svg class="icon postal-address-icon map-marker"><use xlink:href="#icon-map-marker"></use></svg><div><a href="https://maps.apple.com/?q=34.19%2C-118.16" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span class="street postal-address-street"> Mount Wilson Red Box Road and Mt Lowe Rd, </span><span class="city postal-address-city"> Altadena, </span><span class="state postal-address-state"> California </span><span class="zipcode postal-address-zipcode"> 91001 </span></a></div></div> <div class="poi-module-more-info"> More Info </div></div></div></div> </div>   <div class="column-container-column two-column-container-5050-column" data-click="5050col2"> <div class="module poi-module" data-click="poi"  data-map-marker-id="0000017d-0abd-d3be-a57d-2efdd03a0000"   data-map-marker-longitude="-118.02682"   data-map-marker-latitude="34.14331"   data-map-marker-title="Mt. Lowe Brewing Co."   data-module-neighborhood="Arcadia"      data-module-cuisines="Brewery"    data-module-category="restaurants" data-module-id="0000017d-0ab5-d502-a1ff-aff769840000"><div class="poi-module-flex container-media">  <div class="media poi-module-media">   <div class="image poi-module-image"> <figure class="figure"> <picture >    <source  type="image/webp"  srcset="https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/cf02ce7/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/320x213!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F42%2F5f%2Ffe233f9646cb97ebd4eab4d799ff%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-mt-lower-brewery-002.JPG 320w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/8557e7f/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/568x379!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F42%2F5f%2Ffe233f9646cb97ebd4eab4d799ff%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-mt-lower-brewery-002.JPG 568w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/869cabe/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/768x512!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F42%2F5f%2Ffe233f9646cb97ebd4eab4d799ff%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-mt-lower-brewery-002.JPG 768w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/7ac724d/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/1024x683!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F42%2F5f%2Ffe233f9646cb97ebd4eab4d799ff%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-mt-lower-brewery-002.JPG 1024w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/48d8847/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/1200x800!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F42%2F5f%2Ffe233f9646cb97ebd4eab4d799ff%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-mt-lower-brewery-002.JPG 1200w"  sizes="85vw"  >     <img class="image" alt="A glass of beer"  srcset="https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/a5746da/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/320x213!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F42%2F5f%2Ffe233f9646cb97ebd4eab4d799ff%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-mt-lower-brewery-002.JPG 320w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/923ed2d/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/568x379!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F42%2F5f%2Ffe233f9646cb97ebd4eab4d799ff%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-mt-lower-brewery-002.JPG 568w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/4734557/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/768x512!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F42%2F5f%2Ffe233f9646cb97ebd4eab4d799ff%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-mt-lower-brewery-002.JPG 768w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/59ad417/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/1024x683!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F42%2F5f%2Ffe233f9646cb97ebd4eab4d799ff%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-mt-lower-brewery-002.JPG 1024w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/5273cf3/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/1200x800!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F42%2F5f%2Ffe233f9646cb97ebd4eab4d799ff%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-mt-lower-brewery-002.JPG 1200w"  sizes="85vw"    width="1200"   height="800"  src="https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/5273cf3/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/1200x800!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F42%2F5f%2Ffe233f9646cb97ebd4eab4d799ff%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-mt-lower-brewery-002.JPG" decoding="async"  loading="lazy"  >  </picture>   <div class="figure-content"> <div class="figure-credit">(Matt Pawlik)</div> </div>  </figure> </div>   </div>  </div><div class="poi-module-flex container-content"><div class="poi-module-flex container-content-block">  <h2 class="title poi-module-title"> Mt. Lowe Brewing Co. </h2>  <div class="poi-module-categories"><span class="poi-module-categories-icon"><span class="icon category restaurants-icon-fff"></span> </span><span class="neighborhood poi-module-categories-neighborhood"> Arcadia </span>   <span class="cuisine poi-module-categories-cuisine"> Brewery </span>    </div>        <div data-element="description" class="ct-body-1 ct-rich-text-children font-service font-light text-base mt-3">Our favorite 🍺: Bungalow Blonde (blonde ale), Lowe Down (New England IPA), Glitter AF (Raspberry Ale with edible glitter)<br><br><b>Hours:</b> 4 to 9 p.m. Tuesdays to Thursdays; 4 to 10 p.m. Fridays; noon to 10 p.m. Saturdays; noon to 8 p.m. Sundays.</div>    <div class="social poi-module-social">  <div class="phone poi-module-phone"><span class="icon phone-icon-087da1" aria-label="phone"></span> <a class="link phone" href="tel:6262447593" data-social-service="phone" >(626) 244-7593 </a> </div>   <div class="website poi-module-website"><span class="icon globe-icon-087da1"></span> <a class="link" href="http://www.mtlowebrewing.com/" target="_blank" >website</a> </div>   <div class="instagram poi-module-instagram"><span class="icon instagram-icon-087da1"></span> <a class="link" href="https://instagram.com/mtlowebrewing" target="_blank" >instagram</a> </div>  </div>  <div class="postal-address"><svg class="icon postal-address-icon map-marker"><use xlink:href="#icon-map-marker"></use></svg><div><a href="https://maps.apple.com/?q=34.14331%2C-118.02682" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span class="street postal-address-street"> 150 E. St. Joseph St., </span><span class="city postal-address-city"> Arcadia, </span><span class="state postal-address-state"> California </span><span class="zipcode postal-address-zipcode"> 91106 </span></a></div></div> <div class="poi-module-more-info"> More Info </div></div></div></div> </div>  </div></div>   </div><p> </p><p>What’s in a name? A peak and a brewery in and near the San Gabriel Mountains share the name Mt. Lowe. Hike to the peak’s 5,606-foot summit by the less-traveled but highly challenging 5.5-mile trek from Eaton Saddle and reward yourself with a post-trail ale at Mt. Lowe Brewing Co.</p> <p>Park on either side of Mt. Wilson/Red Box Road off the Angeles Crest Highway and find the trailhead with an accompanying sign about professor Thaddeus Lowe, who built the legendary railway along the mountain and an early 20th-century resort at nearby Echo Mountain. Enjoy views of the sprawling San Gabriel Valley and head through the echo-worthy Mueller Tunnel, built in 1942. When you reach a water tower, stay right to head down the Mt. Lowe Motorway and veer left at your next junction. The Mt. Lowe Trail Camp, home to five walk-in campsites at 4,500 feet, is a great spot for a picnic under the oaks before your ascent. Continue on to hike more than 1,000 feet uphill in the next mile to reach Mt. Lowe’s summit, home to an old hitching post and viewing tubes pointed at local peaks. Vistas reveal the downtown L.A. skyline and Catalina Island, on a clear day. Complete the loop back to the water tower and trailhead. </p><div class="enhancement" data-click="enhancement"
    
        data-align-center
    
><div class="google-dfp-ad-wrapper" style="min-height: 270px" data-min-height="270" ><div class="google-dfp-ad-caption">Advertisement</div><div id="google-adf44d6fbd-88a8-4dcd-9222-c862dceb570e" class="google-dfp-ad injected" data-slot-name="/21787098806/web.latimes/travel/storystack_inline"  data-slot-sizes="[[300, 250], [728, 90], [970, 250], [970, 90]]"  data-ad-type="injected"  data-slot-ad-size-maps="[[[1024, 0], [728, 90], [970, 250], [970, 90]], [[0, 0], [300, 250]]]"  data-module-targeting="{&quot;position&quot;:&quot;11&quot;}" ><span class="google-dfp-ad-placeholder"></span></div></div></div><p> </p> <p>Then head to <a class="link" href="http://www.mtlowebrewing.com/" target="_blank" >Mt. Lowe Brewing Co.</a>, which displays old maps and photographs of the mountain and features railway spikes as tap handles. You’re here for the beer, though. Try the locally themed ales, such as the Lowe Down IPA or get a five-taster flight presented on a beautiful (and fitting) log plate.</p> </div>   </div>  </div><div class="story-stack-item" id="19" data-target ><div class="story-stack-item-number"  data-hide-number ><span>19</span></div>  <div  class="story-stack-story">  <h3 class="story-stack-story-title">Mt. Wilson and RT Rogers Brewing Co.</h3>     <div data-element="story-stack-story-body" class="ct-rich-text-children font-body font-normal text-lg leading-7.75 text-primary-text-color clearfix"> <div class="enhancement" data-click="enhancement"
    
        data-align-center
    
