/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F97%2F7f%2F59d6ce0b4b3882d1b48e827438e2%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-highpoint-001.jpg 1200w"  sizes="85vw"    width="1200"   height="800"  src="https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/3001eeb/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/1200x800!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F97%2F7f%2F59d6ce0b4b3882d1b48e827438e2%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-highpoint-001.jpg" decoding="async"  loading="lazy"  >  </picture>   <div class="figure-content"> <div class="figure-credit">(Matt Pawlik)</div> </div>  </figure> </div>   </div>  </div><div class="poi-module-flex container-content"><div class="poi-module-flex container-content-block">  <h2 class="title poi-module-title"> Highpoint Brewing Co. </h2>  <div class="poi-module-categories"><span class="poi-module-categories-icon"><span class="icon category restaurants-icon-fff"></span> </span><span class="neighborhood poi-module-categories-neighborhood"> San Dimas </span>   <span class="cuisine poi-module-categories-cuisine"> Brewery </span>    </div>        <div data-element="description" class="ct-body-1 ct-rich-text-children font-service font-light text-base mt-3"><b>Our favorite 🍺:</b> Dropout (Imperial Stout, Nitro), Bad Kitty (Triple IPA), Belgian Beach Party (Belgian Blonde Ale)<br><br><b>Hours: </b>2 to 8 p.m. Mondays to Wednesdays; 4 to 10 p.m. Thursdays and Fridays; noon to 10 p.m. Saturdays; noon to 8 p.m. Sundays</div>    <div class="social poi-module-social">   <div class="website poi-module-website"><span class="icon globe-icon-087da1"></span> <a class="link" href="https://highpointbrewco.com/craft-beers/" target="_blank" >website</a> </div>   <div class="instagram poi-module-instagram"><span class="icon instagram-icon-087da1"></span> <a class="link" href="https://instagram.com/highpointbrewco" target="_blank" >instagram</a> </div>  </div>  <div class="postal-address"><svg class="icon postal-address-icon map-marker"><use xlink:href="#icon-map-marker"></use></svg><div><a href="https://maps.apple.com/?q=34.10286%2C-117.813904" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span class="street postal-address-street"> 402 W. Arrow Hwy. No. 12, </span><span class="city postal-address-city"> San Dimas, </span><span class="state postal-address-state"> California </span><span class="zipcode postal-address-zipcode"> 91773 </span></a></div></div> <div class="poi-module-more-info"> More Info </div></div></div></div> </div>  </div></div>   </div><p> </p><div class="enhancement" data-click="enhancement"
    
        data-align-center
    
><div class="google-dfp-ad-wrapper" style="min-height: 270px" data-min-height="270" ><div class="google-dfp-ad-caption">Advertisement</div><div id="google-adae687e9e-2b47-4b7c-8659-0cdebfe042b8" class="google-dfp-ad injected" data-slot-name="/21787098806/web.latimes/travel/storystack_inline"  data-slot-sizes="[[300, 250], [728, 90], [970, 250], [970, 90]]"  data-ad-type="injected"  data-slot-ad-size-maps="[[[1024, 0], [728, 90], [970, 250], [970, 90]], [[0, 0], [300, 250]]]"  data-module-targeting="{&quot;position&quot;:&quot;12&quot;}" ><span class="google-dfp-ad-placeholder"></span></div></div></div><p> </p><p>Looking for a most excellent adventure? Head to San Dimas, famous in pop culture for housing Bill and Ted (from the 1989 sci-fi comedy film “Bill and Ted’s Excellent Adventure”), for a totally rad 2.5-mile trek, awesome views and a righteous reward post-hike. </p> <p>Park at Horsethief Canyon Park and find the trailhead next to a gazebo at the north end of the lot. At the horse track, turn left to flank the dog park, passing under willows, palms and pines and eventually looping back to hug the hill ahead. Make a left when you see a steep trail behind a white gate — and head uphill for a killer challenge to the hill’s top. At the top, the panoramic views of San Dimas and the endlessly expanding valley are epic. Enjoy the views from a bench between two pines or a picnic table under a welcoming willow. Look for Mt. Baldy’s prominent peak to the east before taking the north trail down into the canyon, where pines and oaks become prevalent. At the next junction, take a right onto Poison Oak Trail (you won’t see much of the troublesome plant) to pass canyon walls and reach the ruins of an old stone chimney. Here, take a right and follow the trail markers leading you through Sycamore Canyon, past an equestrian center and back to the trailhead. Before leaving, consider visiting neighboring <a class="link" href="https://parks.lacounty.gov/san-dimas-canyon-natural-area-and-nature-center/" target="_blank" >San Dimas Canyon Nature Center</a> and Puddingstone Reservoir at Frank G. Bonelli Park to the south. </p> <p>Otherwise, head to the other local watering hole, <a class="link" href="https://highpointbrewco.com/craft-beers/" target="_blank" >Highpoint Brewing</a>. Try its beer deal of the day or get a tasting flight and, if you’re lucky, there’ll be trivia or bingo going.</p> </div>   </div>  </div><div class="story-stack-item" id="21" data-target ><div class="story-stack-item-number"  data-hide-number ><span>21</span></div>  <div  class="story-stack-story">  <h3 class="story-stack-story-title">Santa Fe Dam Recreational Area and Nova Brewing Co.</h3>     <div data-element="story-stack-story-body" class="ct-rich-text-children font-body font-normal text-lg leading-7.75 text-primary-text-color clearfix"> <div class="enhancement" data-click="enhancement"
    
        data-align-center
    
>   <div class="column-container two-column-container-5050" >  <div class="column-container-row two-column-container-5050-row">  <div class="column-container-column two-column-container-5050-column" data-click="5050col1"> <div class="module poi-module" data-click="poi"  data-map-marker-id="0000017c-f170-d385-abfc-f77c6f2e0000"   data-map-marker-longitude="-117.951646"   data-map-marker-latitude="34.114369"   data-map-marker-title="Santa Fe Dam Recreational Area"   data-module-neighborhood="Irwindale"     data-module-hike-difficulty="Easy"     data-module-hike-length="4.0"   data-module-category="parks-trails" data-module-subcategory="Urban Trail" data-module-subcategory-filter-id="parks-trails_00000178-1e5a-dff5-abff-de5a13ce0000" data-module-id="0000017c-f172-d385-abfc-f77e748e0000"><div class="poi-module-flex container-media">  <div class="media poi-module-media">   <div class="image poi-module-image"> <figure class="figure"> <picture >    <source  type="image/webp"  srcset="https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/0c94ca7/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/320x213!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2F20%2F443dc671491f90dcdc9031c22922%2Fsanta-fe-dam-2.jpg 320w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/da9a33b/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/568x379!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2F20%2F443dc671491f90dcdc9031c22922%2Fsanta-fe-dam-2.jpg 568w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/61b3822/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/768x512!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2F20%2F443dc671491f90dcdc9031c22922%2Fsanta-fe-dam-2.jpg 768w,https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/53be4a7/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/1024x683!/format/webp/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaw