81cdecc8%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-sfv-brew-co.jpg 1200w"  sizes="85vw"    width="1200"   height="800"  src="https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/b422c02/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4032x2688+0+168/resize/1200x800!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcf%2F6f%2F295964504aab9640fe8d81cdecc8%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-sfv-brew-co.jpg" decoding="async"  loading="lazy"  >  </picture>   <div class="figure-content"> <div class="figure-credit">(Matt Pawlik)</div> </div>  </figure> </div>   </div>  </div><div class="poi-module-flex container-content"><div class="poi-module-flex container-content-block">  <h2 class="title poi-module-title"> San Fernando Brewing Co. </h2>  <div class="poi-module-categories"><span class="poi-module-categories-icon"><span class="icon category restaurants-icon-fff"></span> </span><span class="neighborhood poi-module-categories-neighborhood"> San Fernando </span>   <span class="cuisine poi-module-categories-cuisine"> Brewery </span>    </div>        <div data-element="description" class="ct-body-1 ct-rich-text-children font-service font-light text-base mt-3"><b>Our favorite 🍺: </b>O’Melveny Red Ale (Amber), Stoney Point Stout (Stout), Wolfskill IPA (West Coast IPA)<br><br><b>Hours:</b> noon to 10 p.m. Thursdays to Saturdays; noon to 7 p.m. Sundays</div>    <div class="social poi-module-social">  <div class="phone poi-module-phone"><span class="icon phone-icon-087da1" aria-label="phone"></span> <a class="link phone" href="tel:8187456175" data-social-service="phone" >(818) 745-6175 </a> </div>   <div class="website poi-module-website"><span class="icon globe-icon-087da1"></span> <a class="link" href="http://www.sanfernandobrewingcompany.com/" target="_blank" >website</a> </div>   <div class="instagram poi-module-instagram"><span class="icon instagram-icon-087da1"></span> <a class="link" href="https://instagram.com/sanfernandobrewingco" target="_blank" >instagram</a> </div>  </div>  <div class="postal-address"><svg class="icon postal-address-icon map-marker"><use xlink:href="#icon-map-marker"></use></svg><div><a href="https://maps.apple.com/?q=34.283367%2C-118.432066" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span class="street postal-address-street"> 425 Park Ave., </span><span class="city postal-address-city"> San Fernando, </span><span class="state postal-address-state"> California </span><span class="zipcode postal-address-zipcode"> 91340 </span></a></div></div> <div class="poi-module-more-info"> More Info </div></div></div></div> </div>  </div></div>   </div><p> </p><p>The hardest climbs should reward with the best views and brews. O’Melveny Park is arguably home to the best overlook of the San Fernando Valley. </p> <p>The namesake loop trail reaches the park’s high point, 2,730-foot Mission Point, after a challenging and scenic ascent above the 672-acre green space (second in size only to Griffith Park in Los Angeles). It’s also home to a historic grapefruit grove and a sprawling picnic area under oaks, sycamores and eucalyptus. In addition to growing citrus, land donor Henry O’Melveny also grazed cattle and bred bulldogs, making it a perfect spot to work out with your pooch. Scenery includes giant sandstone walls, sprawling meadows and the juxtaposition of rolling hills and rocky outcroppings. After two miles, there is an option for an additional challenge: Mission Point. </p><div class="enhancement" data-click="enhancement"
    
        data-align-center
    
><div class="google-dfp-ad-wrapper" style="min-height: 270px" data-min-height="270" ><div class="google-dfp-ad-caption">Advertisement</div><div id="google-ada06529cb-9d00-41be-8423-5cec0497f958" class="google-dfp-ad injected" data-slot-name="/21787098806/web.latimes/travel/storystack_inline"  data-slot-sizes="[[300, 250], [728, 90], [970, 250], [970, 90]]"  data-ad-type="injected"  data-slot-ad-size-maps="[[[1024, 0], [728, 90], [970, 250], [970, 90]], [[0, 0], [300, 250]]]"  data-module-targeting="{&quot;position&quot;:&quot;15&quot;}" ><span class="google-dfp-ad-placeholder"></span></div></div></div><p> </p> <p>After working up a sweat, go rehydrate at <a class="link" href="http://www.sanfernandobrewingcompany.com/" target="_blank" >San Fernando Brewing Co.</a> for a post-adventure reward. It serves beer named after local landmarks, such as the eponymous O’Melveny Red Ale and Stoney Point Stout.</p><div class="enhancement" data-click="enhancement"
    
        data-align-center
    
