rnia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2F52%2F71a8fe76437bb0f1bf7426a5ccdf%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-san-pedro-breweries.jpg 1200w"  sizes="85vw"    width="1200"   height="800"  src="https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/05f7b73/2147483647/strip/true/crop/3264x2176+0+136/resize/1200x800!/quality/80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2F52%2F71a8fe76437bb0f1bf7426a5ccdf%2Fla-photos-handouts-la-tr-ales-and-trails-san-pedro-breweries.jpg" decoding="async"  loading="lazy"  >  </picture>   <div class="figure-content"> <div class="figure-credit">(Matt Pawlik)</div> </div>  </figure> </div>   </div>  </div><div class="poi-module-flex container-content"><div class="poi-module-flex container-content-block">  <h2 class="title poi-module-title"> Brouwerij West </h2>  <div class="poi-module-categories"><span class="poi-module-categories-icon"><span class="icon category restaurants-icon-fff"></span> </span><span class="neighborhood poi-module-categories-neighborhood"> San Pedro </span>   <span class="cuisine poi-module-categories-cuisine"> Brewery </span>    </div>        <div data-element="description" class="ct-body-1 ct-rich-text-children font-service font-light text-base mt-3"><b>Our favorite 🍺: </b>Popfuji (Pilsner), Picnic Lightning (Hazy IPA), Dog Ate My Homework (Blackberry Ale)<br><br><b>Hours:</b> 3 to 10 p.m. Wednesdays to Fridays; noon to 10 p.m. Saturdays; 11 a.m. to 9 p.m. Sundays</div>    <div class="social poi-module-social">  <div class="phone poi-module-phone"><span class="icon phone-icon-087da1" aria-label="phone"></span> <a class="link phone" href="tel:3108339330" data-social-service="phone" >(310) 833-9330 </a> </div>   <div class="website poi-module-website"><span class="icon globe-icon-087da1"></span> <a class="link" href="https://www.brouwerijwest.com/" target="_blank" >website</a> </div>   <div class="instagram poi-module-instagram"><span class="icon instagram-icon-087da1"></span> <a class="link" href="https://instagram.com/brouwerijwest" target="_blank" >instagram</a> </div>  </div>  <div class="postal-address"><svg class="icon postal-address-icon map-marker"><use xlink:href="#icon-map-marker"></use></svg><div><a href="https://maps.apple.com/?q=33.72689%2C-118.280513" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span class="street postal-address-street"> 110 E. 22nd St., </span><span class="city postal-address-city"> San Pedro, </span><span class="state postal-address-state"> California </span><span class="zipcode postal-address-zipcode"> 90731 </span></a></div></div> <div class="poi-module-more-info"> More Info </div></div></div></div> </div>  </div></div>   </div><p> </p><p>Looking for falcons, fig trees and fermentables? Try the two-mile park-to-park-to-park urban foray in San Pedro that focuses on big ocean views and big trees. </p> <p>Start at the southeast corner of Point Fermin Park and walk north along the cliff-adjacent path. Look for coastal views, giant Moreton Bay fig trees and the 1874 Point Fermin Lighthouse. Hug the coast for consistent ocean vistas and then climb the prominent hill to Angels Gate Park, home to the Fort MacArthur Museum, Korean Bell of Friendship (a bronze bell that was a gift of the South Korean government) and even more expansive seascapes. The 360-degree views are awe-inspiring, but scan the skies for the true treasure among the clouds: peregrine falcons. A bit north you’ll find Wilders Addition Park, which has a dirt bluffs trail under the palms, and White Point Nature Preserve, a 102-acre coastal chaparral preserve with a 1.3-mile loop and perfect turnaround point. If you want to extend your walk, head to Cabrillo Beach, just one mile from Point Fermin Park. </p> <p>When you’re ready for a post-walk treat, head to <a class="link" href="https://www.brouwerijwest.com/" target="_blank" >Brouwerij West</a>, home to grand ales in a massive warehouse.</p> <p></p> <p></p> </div>   </div>  </div><div class="story-stack-item" id="30" data-target ><div class="story-stack-item-number"  data-hide-number ><span>30</span></div>  <div  class="story-stack-story">  <h3 class="story-stack-story-title">Rocky Peak Park and Hand-Brewed Beer</h3>     <div data-element="story-stack-story-body" class="ct-rich-text-children font-body font-normal text-lg leading-7.75 text-primary-text-color clearfix"> <div class="enhancement" data-click="enhancement"
    
